<p>
<strong><sup>*</sup>Note:</strong>
In Java,
You can  do all sorts
of interesting things
with HTML,
sometimes even with CSS.
Try this in a program:
</p>
<pre style="font-family: 'Lucida Console', 'Courier New', monospace; font-size: 90%; padding-left:3em;">private static final String labelText   =
    "&lt;html>"
    + "&lt;span style='color: red;'>Little miss &lt;/span>"
    + "&lt;span style='color: green; font-size: 200%;'>"
    + "    Stuffit"
    + "&lt;/span>&lt;br>"
    + "&lt;span style='color: blue;'>sat on &lt;/span>"
    + "&lt;span style='color: #7f00ff; "
    + "font-size: 200%; font-family: arial bold'>"
    +     "a Muppet"
    + "&lt;/span>&amp;#x1F911;"
    + "&lt;/html>";
...
JLable label = new JLabel( labelText );</pre>
<p>
